HEADWORD: Caseharden
<hw>Case"hard`en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
subject to a process which converts the surface of iron into
steel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To render insensible to good influences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Casehardened</ent>⟦br⟧
